reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 6, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Fits Perfectly - GE Model GSD5130D00WW
reviews.reviewText: Dimensions and wheels fit this older model perfectly! Inverted V-shaped dish supports are a fantastic improvement over the old tines.Original silverware basket does not fit and so consider also buying the recommended new silverware basket.One star off value for money... the cost of this rack is 1/3 the cost of a new dishwasher and yet, this is our choice because our old dishwasher works perfectly well, but the lower rack had rusted through.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 13, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Fit perfectly in our dishwasher.
reviews.reviewText: I like it because it works in our old dishwasher and I don’t have to buy a new dishwasher.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 1, 2017
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Already Rusting After a Few Months
reviews.reviewText: Calling this rack Junk is being kind. It's slightly narrower than the original part so the wheels constantly fall off the tracks, usually when it's fully loaded. There are already tiny rust specs in some joints after a few months of normal use, which must be patched using food grade sealant or they will quickly spread. The arrangement of dish holders is 'ok'; not as good as the original factory part, but adequate.This is the second replacement I have purchased. The first completely rusted out in sections and began to fall apart after 14 months. The original factory part lasted many, many years longer. Now I'm left with a perfectly functioning dishwasher that requires a new lower rack every 18 months and new upper rack every 24 months, because GE can't be bothered to produce quality replacement parts. It's disgraceful. What is even more disgraceful is charging this much for this piece of garbage.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 12, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Great OEM rack replacement. Just kind of a bit pricey but understandable.
reviews.reviewText: Great OEM replacement. May cost a bit more than desired, but for its bulk of storage/shipping, is understandable. Good fit.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 18, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars The price was good , but the product was disappointing!
reviews.reviewText: The lower dishwasher basket casters were bent and did not roll in easily. It seems like it is almost too small for the dishwasher and easily comes off the track when rolling the basket in and out. I'm very disappointed in this product too and I already threw out the original rack, so I'm stuck again! Very disappointed!!!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 9, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Smaller wheels stay on track
reviews.reviewText: Wheels are smaller than original but no issues so far.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 5, 2016
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good product, good price
reviews.reviewText: Good product, good price, fits my Hotpoint perfectly, and the coating and dish prongs are well set up; the only slight draw back is that the new wheels are still fairly thin, and so you would want to salvage your "old rear wheels" and put those on to the new rack, as the new wheels are too thin at the rear of the new rack, tend to have the rack slide off the track or ledges.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 30, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars For my GE Triton GSD5500G dishwasher
reviews.reviewText: As noted by other buyers, I did have to switch out the wheels, which I kept from my discontinued lower rack and ordered a new silverware (WD28X265) basket from Amazon.com Services LLC. The wheel replacement was easy and the rack fits perfectly. Hopefully will get a few more years use from my 16 year old dishwasher.

The front wheels are narrow there are 4 of them, the rear is thin, the front ones are wider and the rack does not fall in the dishwasher. The rack is the same but the thin wheels make it not usable. But I removed the front four wheels and put them on the new rack and all was well, again the original had wide wheels twice as wide as the rear?? Otherwise, it's fine, but if you don't have wide wheels to swap them it will not fit properly. It also seems a bit pricy for a wire rack. But thay are like most parts expensive.
